Maintainer: Ben Wiseman <benjamin.h.wiseman@gmail.com>
Description: Sentiment scoring from sentence embeddings, with most of the setup handled for
  you: a sentence-embedding model turns text into vectors and a small bundled scoring head
  returns a score in the range -1 (negative) to 1 (positive). The default backend
  ('multilingual-e5-small') runs on-device with no TensorFlow and no API key; legacy
  Universal Sentence Encoder backends remain available. Benchmarks on public review corpora
  are reported at <https://benwiseman.github.io/sentiment.ai/#Benchmarks>. The embedding
  vectors are also returned for use in other analyses.
URL: https://benwiseman.github.io/sentiment.ai/,
